No, no, not when she was a widow, no. Used to have the Evening Sentinal, later on, when she married again, of course these young men wanted to have a look and things like that. But we never had one at home, we might have borrowed from next door, next d
oor had one, we might have borrowed it to have a look at theirs me mother might have done but as a youngster I didn't trouble much about newspapers, No.
