 And that's when me mother had a family group, all dressed in black sort of style, and I always remember she got this one. And well I don't know what really happened to it. I do remember that me father had a gun, he used to have a dog a fox terrier () dog
,
 and me father had a gun and they weren't bullets then, bend of powder, powder bags and I think they must have had to make their own charges up at that particular time and where the Colliery is now were all fields, there was the old brickyard there, and t
h
ere used to be some rabbits down there, and the Council Tip was partly down there, and they used to get rabbits and that down there and I remember him going, and me mother pawned the gun, and he used to go shooting down there, and get a rabbit or two some
t
ime you know, but this dog, I always remember this dog and all. And he kept pigeons, I always remember this dog, a fox terrier, and he'd kill any kind of vermin really, rats or anything. And there were quite a few, quite a few of his old pals wanted this 
d
og and me mother wouldn't part with it, but eventually me mother always thought that someone gave it some poison or something but didn't give it enough to finish it off, something happened, it kind of, a lot of its hair came off, you know and one of his o
ld pals was brother-in-law to a farmer and in the end, when it got in really poor condition this chap shot it behind a haystack in the yard, and buried it behind the haystack.
